==Further reading==
'''In English''':
* [[John Bell (historian)|Bell, John]]. ''[[Invaders from the North]]: How Canada Conquered the Comic Book Universe''. Toronto: [[Dundurn Press]], 2006. ISBN 978-1-55002-659-7
* Bell, John. ''[[Guardians of the North]]: The National Superhero in Canadian Comic-Book Art''. [[National Archives of Canada]], 1992. ISBN 0-662-19347-4
* Bell, John. ''[[Canuck Comics]]: A Guide to Comic Books Published in Canada''. Matrix Books, 1986. ISBN 0-921101-00-7
* [[Peter Desbarats|Desbarats,Peter]]; and [[Terry Mosher|Mosher, Terry]]. ''The Hecklers: A History of Canadian Political Cartooning''. [[McClelland and Stewart]], 1979. ISBN 978-0-7710-2686-7
* [[Michael Hirsh (producer)|Hirsh, Michael]]; and [[Patrick Loubert|Loubert, Patrick]]. ''[[The Great Canadian Comic Books]]''. Peter Martin Associates, 1971. ISBN 0-88778-065-2
* Theaker, Dan. ''An Introduction to Canadian Comic Books: A Bibliography and Price Guide to Canadian Comic Books, 1941-1985''. Aurora Books, 1986

